.SH "Field Documentation"
.PP 
.SS "int change_output_size = 0"
Size of a change output in bytes, determined by the output type\&. 
.SS "int change_spend_size = 0"
Size of the input to spend a change output in virtual bytes\&. 
.SS "bool m_avoid_partial_spends = false"
When true, always spend all (up to OUTPUT_GROUP_MAX_ENTRIES) or none of the outputs associated with the same address\&. This helps reduce privacy leaks resulting from address reuse\&. Dust outputs are not eligible to be added to output groups and thus not considered\&. 
.SS "\fBCAmount\fP m_change_fee {0}"
Cost of creating the change output\&. 
.SS "\fBCAmount\fP m_cost_of_change {0}"
Cost of creating the change output + cost of spending the change output in the future\&. 
.SS "\fBCFeeRate\fP m_discard_feerate"
If the cost to spend a change output at the discard feerate exceeds its value, drop it to fees\&. 
.SS "\fBCFeeRate\fP m_effective_feerate"
The targeted feerate of the transaction being built\&. 
.SS "bool m_include_unsafe_inputs = false"
When true, allow unsafe coins to be selected during \fBCoin\fP Selection\&. This may spend unconfirmed outputs: 1) Received from other wallets, 2) replacing other txs, 3) that have been replaced\&. 
.SS "\fBCFeeRate\fP m_long_term_feerate"
The feerate estimate used to estimate an upper bound on what should be sufficient to spend the change output sometime in the future\&. 
.SS "std::optional<int> m_max_tx_weight {std::nullopt}"
The maximum weight for this transaction\&. 
.SS "\fBCAmount\fP m_min_change_target {0}"
Mininmum change to target in Knapsack solver and CoinGrinder: select coins to cover the payment and at least this value of change\&. 
.SS "bool m_subtract_fee_outputs = false"
Indicate that we are subtracting the fee from outputs 
.SS "uint32_t m_version {\fBCTransaction::CURRENT_VERSION\fP}"
The version of the transaction we are trying to create\&. 
.SS "\fBCAmount\fP min_viable_change {0}"
Minimum amount for creating a change output\&. If change budget is smaller than min_change then we forgo creation of change output\&. 
.SS "\fBFastRandomContext\fP& rng_fast"
Randomness to use in the context of coin selection\&. 
.SS "int tx_noinputs_size = 0"
Size of the transaction before coin selection, consisting of the header and recipient output(s), excluding the inputs and change output(s)\&. 

